---
description: Core engineering standards for this project. Applies to every file, every task, every agent.
alwaysApply: true
---

## Commands
- Dev: `npm run dev`
- Build: `npm run build`
- Lint: `npm run lint`
- Test: `npm run test`
- Sync graph: `npm run sync`
- Install: `npm install` (never `yarn` or `pnpm`)

## TypeScript
- Strict mode is on ‚Äî never use `any`. Use `unknown` and narrow it.
- Named exports only ‚Äî no default exports anywhere in the codebase.
- Prefer `type` over `interface` for data shapes.
- All function parameters and return types must be explicitly typed.
- Never use `@ts-ignore` ‚Äî fix the type error instead.
- Never use `as unknown as X` to force a type cast ‚Äî find the real type.

## Code style
- `const` over `let`. Never `var`.
- ES modules only ‚Äî `import/export`, never `require`.
- Destructure imports: `import { foo } from 'bar'` not `import bar from 'bar'`.
- No barrel `index.ts` re-exports that include everything ‚Äî explicit named exports only.
- Functions under 40 lines. If longer, extract.

## Hard prohibitions
- No `console.log`, `console.warn`, `console.debug` in production code paths.
- `console.error` only inside catch blocks.
- Never commit `.env`, `.env.local`, or any env file that is not `.env.example`.
- Never hardcode secrets, tokens, or connection strings.

## Git
- Conventional commits: `type(scope): description`
- Types: `feat` `fix` `refactor` `chore` `perf` `docs` `test`
- Message under 72 characters.
- Run `/preflight` before every commit.

## Project structure
- `src/app/` ‚Äî Next.js App Router pages and API routes
- `src/components/` ‚Äî React components
- `src/lib/` ‚Äî Shared utilities and helpers
- `public/` ‚Äî Static assets (graph.json, images)
- `.claude/` ‚Äî AI skills and commands
- `.cursor/` ‚Äî AI agents and rules

## When uncertain
- Run `npm run build` after any series of changes ‚Äî catches type errors.
- Read `CONTEXT.md` before making architectural decisions.
- If a pattern already exists in the codebase, follow it ‚Äî don't introduce a new one.
